ator ($2^{\\circ}-20^{\\circ}$N),\nand dry air descends at the poles ($90^{\\circ}-66^{\\circ}$S) and just south of\nthe equator ($12^{\\circ}$S$-2^{\\circ}$N). Our analysis finds more complex\nstructure near the equator than accounted for in previous circulation models.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 8 May 2019 22:47:17 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-07-17"}
