ermore, STDs decreased. In-vivo, the blurring correction removed fat bias\non T1/T2 from a rim of about 7-8 mm width adjacent to fatty structures.\n  CONCLUSION: The blurring correction for spiral MRF yields improved\nquantitative maps in the presence of water and fat.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 9 May 2019 12:08:40 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-05-28"}
